06/04/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Montenegrins voted on Sunday (April 6th) in the first presidential election since the country's independence in May 2006. 
Incumbent president Filip Vujanovic, nominated by the ruling Democratic Party of Socialists-Social Democratic Party coalition, faces challengers Srdjan Milic from the Socialist People's Party, Andrija Mandic from the Serbian List and Nebojsa Medojevic from the Movement for Change. 
Polls suggest Vujanovic is the frontrunner. 
(Beta, AFP, Focus - 06/04/08)
